# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# WHITELIST: publish ONLY the source in src/ + what is needed to run it.
# Everything else (17 GB ChatTS ckpt, ESA/space-ai datasets, papers, vendored
# repos, secrets, tests, legacy, data) stays local. This is a deny-by-default
# .gitignore: ignore every top-level entry, then re-include the few we publish.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
/*

# …re-include the code, the run essentials, and the experiment reports:
!/src/
!/reports/
!/pyproject.toml
!/uv.lock
!/.python-version
!/README.md
!/.gitignore

# Never track secrets or caches/artefacts, even inside the re-included tree:
.env
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
